    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-12T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-12T18:00:00-05:00" n="574"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-12T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>423. Your 579, November 9, 1 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d574fn31">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You may inform Japanese Government that this Government proposes to address the
                    Belgian Government as follows and state that this Government hopes the Japanese
                    Government may make an identic communication: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your note of November 4,
                                1920,<note n="31" xml:id="d574fn32">Not printed.</note> referring to
                            the fact that the representatives of the American, British, French and
                            Japanese Groups had voted, at the Consortium meeting held at New York
                            last month, to approve the admission of a Belgian Banking Group in the
                            Chinese Consortium, subject to the approval of the respective
                            Governments of the parties concerned.</p>
                        <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that this Government approves of
                            the admission to the Consortium of a Belgian Banking <pb facs="0693"
                                n="595" xml:id="pg_595"/> Group on the same terms as those accepted
                            and approved by the American, British, French and Japanese Banking
                            Groups.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Acting upon suggestion of Japanese Government this text is being submitted to
                    British and French Governments with a view to its use in identic communications
                    to the Belgian Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
